             sworn. I live at <placeName id="t18060917-30-crimeloc161">Isleworth</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18060917-30-crimeloc161" type="placeName" value="Isleworth"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18060917-30-crimeloc161" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18060917-30-off159 t18060917-30-crimeloc161"></join>. I saw the prisoner Walker on the 13th of August, about four o'clock in the afternoon, take the chains out of a ditch adjoining Mr. Upfull's garden and the road. I followed him about two hundred yards, I overtook him, I asked Walker where he got them chains, he immediately said he had taken them out of Mr. Upfull's garden; on the Friday before he had put them in the ditch till that time, and he was going to sell them.</p>
               <p>Q. You have not said a word about the other prisoner. - A. The other prisoner was present when he took the chains, and when he saw me he ran away.</p>
               <p>(The property identified by the prosecutor.)</p>
               <p>Walker's Defence. I was walking up this lane, I saw this chain laying in the ditch, I did not think any harm taking it; we were bringing them home, and Mr. Hardy took us to his house, and put us in his closet and sent for Mr. Upfull.</p>
               <p>Perryham was not put on his defence.</p>
               <p>PERRYHAM - <rs id="t18060917-30-verdict162" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18060917-30-verdict162" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               NOT GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>WALKER - <rs id="t18060917-30-verdict163" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18060917-30-verdict163" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>, aged 12.</p>
